	<font size="-1"><b><b>FCC Chairman Kennard To Give Special Luncheon Address At The 2000 International CES</b></b></font>

	<p>Arlington, VA - Dec, 29 1999
	<BR>
	WHO:	Federal Communications Commission (FCC) Chairman William E. Kennard  <P>
WHAT:	Special Luncheon Address <P>
WHEN: 	Friday, January 7, 2000, 11:45am-1:00pm <P>
WHERE: 	2000 International CES, Las Vegas Convention Center, N259 <P>
WHY: 	Kennard to Discuss IPTV in the Digital Age <P>
As chairman of the FCC, William Kennard is the key government official overseeing the technologies driving our new digital economy.  Under Chairman Kennard, the FCC's oversight of the radio, broadcasting, telephone, satellite and cable industries has helped ensure U.S. leadership in the worldwide digital revolution. <P>
CES is the world's leading source for the latest consumer technology information.  Among the more than 90,000 international industry professionals expected at CES, are the top government officials who come to Vegas to learn about and discuss what's new and hot for consumers' workstyles and lifestyles.  Kennard is one of the top federal agency officials speaking at the 2000 International CES.   <P>
For a complete line-up of CES events and conferences, visit www.CESweb.org. <P>
WHO:	Federal Communications Commission (FCC) Chairman William E. Kennard  WHAT:	Special Luncheon Address WHEN: 	Friday, January 7, 2000, 11:45am-1:00pm WHERE: 	2000 International CES, Las Vegas Convention Center, N259 WHY: 		Kennard to Discuss IPTV in the Digital Age <P>
As chairman of the FCC, William Kennard is the key government official overseeing the technologies driving our new digital economy.  Under Chairman Kennard, the FCC's oversight of the radio, broadcasting, telephone, satellite and cable industries has helped ensure U.S. leadership in the worldwide digital revolution. <P>
CES is the world's leading source for the latest consumer technology information.  Among the more than 90,000 international industry professionals expected at CES, are the top government officials who come to Vegas to learn about and discuss what's new and hot for consumers' workstyles and lifestyles.  Kennard is one of the top federal agency officials speaking at the 2000 International CES.   <P>
 To RSVP for the luncheon, please call: 703-907-7979 (CEA Virginia Headquarters) or 702-943-3575 (CES Press Room) <P>
